					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">No date</hi></p>						

						<p>States that Iṟandakālameḍutta Aḻagiya-Maṇavāḷadāsaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Periyāḻvār jumped down from the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> and lost his life as a protest against lapses of worship in the temple. With the restoration of worship certain temple honours were shown to (the effigy of) this person. <hi rend="bold">The record cites the cyclic year Saumya, Tai. 22, Friday</hi> which correspond to <hi rend="bold">1610 A.D., January 19.</hi> Palaeography supports this dating of the record.</p>						

						</summary>
